# SQL Directory

This directory contains all SQL for the MLB analytics platform database. Files are organized into numbered folders so the apply order is explicit and reproducible. Within each folder, files are numbered for the same reason.

## How to apply

Run folders in ascending numeric order. Within each folder, run files in ascending numeric order. Every file is wrapped in a transaction so failures are isolated.

Apply a single file:

```bash
psql -U your_user -d your_db -f sql/010_extensions/001_extensions.sql
```

Apply an entire folder in order:

```bash
for f in sql/010_extensions/*.sql; do psql -U your_user -d your_db -f "$f"; done
```

Repeat for each numbered folder in sequence.

## Folder map

| Folder | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `010_extensions/` | Required extensions (`pgcrypto`, `citext`, `btree_gist`) and optional ones (`pgaudit`, `pg_cron`, `pgvector`) |
| `020_schemas/` | Schema creation for all logical layers: `meta`, `ref`, `raw_*`, `stg`, `core`, `ml`, `ops`, `auth`, `api`, `mart`, `util` |
| `030_meta/` | Source system registry, ingest runs, source files, payload hash deduplication, and ingest errors |
| `040_raw/` | Source-faithful landing tables for Retrosheet, Chadwick, Statcast, MLB StatsAPI, Lahman, FanGraphs, Baseball Reference, ESPN, and odds providers |
| `050_staging/` | Identity bridges and source conformance tables that reconcile player, team, venue, and game identifiers across sources |
| `060_core/` | Canonical baseball warehouse: players, teams, venues, games, rosters, plate appearances, pitches, and source lineage maps |
| `070_ml_ops/` | Model registry, feature store, training runs, backtests, predictions, simulations, live polling, job scheduling, API contracts, and serving views |
| `080_functions/` | All `util.*` functions: timestamp triggers, hashing helpers, ingest lifecycle, validation, normalization, key construction, and ML/ops helpers |
| `090_constraints_indexes/` | Indexes and constraints separated from table DDL for independent iteration and tuning |

## Schema quick reference

| Schema | Role |
|--------|------|
| `meta` | Ingestion control plane — source systems, ingest runs, file registry, payload hashes, errors |
| `ref` | Stable lookup tables and enumerations |
| `raw_retrosheet` | Retrosheet event file records (info, start, play, sub, comment, data, adjustment) |
| `raw_chadwick` | Chadwick structured extractions (`cwevent`, `cwgame`, `cwsub`) |
| `raw_lahman` | Lahman historical tables (people, batting, pitching, fielding, teams) |
| `raw_statcast` | Baseball Savant / Statcast pitch-level exports |
| `raw_mlbapi` | MLB StatsAPI request/payload history and expanded endpoint tables |
| `raw_fangraphs` | FanGraphs request and payload captures |
| `raw_bref` | Baseball Reference captures |
| `raw_espn` | ESPN captures |
| `raw_odds` | Sportsbook and odds-source payloads |
| `stg` | Cross-source identity and game conformance bridges |
| `core` | Canonical baseball entities and gameplay facts |
| `ml` | Model registry, feature store, training runs, backtests, predictions, simulations |
| `ops` | Job scheduling, queuing, retries, dead letters, live polling, refresh logs |
| `auth` | Users, workspaces, service accounts, API keys, entitlements |
| `api` | API plans, request logs, idempotency, webhooks |
| `mart` | Read-optimized serving views and materialized views |
| `util` | Shared helper functions and triggers |

## Key function families (`080_functions/`)

| Family | Representative functions |
|--------|--------------------------|
| Timestamp triggers | `util.touch_updated_at()`, `util.core_touch_updated_at()` |
| Hashing / deduplication | `util.sha256_text()`, `util.register_payload_hash()` |
| Ingest lifecycle | `util.start_ingest_run()`, `util.finish_ingest_run()` |
| Validation / normalization | `util.normalize_retrosheet_record_type()`, `util.normalize_team_code()` |
| Key construction | `util.build_retrosheet_game_id()`, `util.build_pa_key()`, `util.build_pitch_key()` |
| ML / live-ops helpers | `util.should_stop_live_polling()`, `util.safe_prediction_rank_score()` |

## Notes

- `010_extensions/002_optional_extensions.sql` contains commented-out extensions. Uncomment only those available in your environment.
- `090_constraints_indexes/` has no `001_` file — indexing for extensions and base schemas is handled implicitly.
- `070_ml_ops/` covers both ML and ops tables **and** includes `auth` and `api` schema objects. Apply all files in that folder before moving to `080_functions/`.
- For design rationale behind any schema, see the corresponding document in `docs/`.